<title>SINGAPORE: Powermatic half year loss worsens.</title>
<headline>Powermatic half year loss worsens.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1996-11-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months ended August 31 1996</p>
<p>	   (in millions of S$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net loss			   0.85	vs	 0.06</p>
<p>    Group share (cents) (loss)   0.50	vs	 0.04 (loss)</p>
<p>    Turnover			  46.79	vs	44.19</p>
<p>    Other income		     0.01	vs	 0.21</p>
<p>    Pre-tax loss		     0.81	vs	 0.02</p>
<p>    Tax				  0.04	vs	 0.04</p>
<p>    Depreciation, amortisation   0.39	vs	 0.48</p>
<p>Note - Powermatic Data Systems Ltd said the group's performance was affected by price erosion due to the highly competitive market for Local Area Network (LAN) products. It said it suffered a net loss due to the poor performance of its U.S subsidiary.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703080)</p>
